The paper deals with approximation algorithms for Holant problems, which are a type of constraint satisfaction problem. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses techniques related to graph polynomials, which could place it in the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the computational phase transition of 2-state spin systems on cubic graphs, which could relate to information theory (cs.IT).
